1
00:00:01,710 --> 00:00:03,880
(Episode 41)

2
00:00:09,580 --> 00:00:10,580
Mom!

3
00:00:11,350 --> 00:00:12,350
Am I a twin?

4
00:00:13,990 --> 00:00:15,490
I'm asking, am I a twin?

5
00:00:17,420 --> 00:00:19,620
What are you talking about?

6
00:00:19,620 --> 00:00:20,730
A twin?

7
00:00:21,260 --> 00:00:22,390
That's ridiculous.

8
00:00:24,160 --> 00:00:26,360
What's wrong with me again?

9
00:00:28,370 --> 00:00:29,530
Are you crying?

10
00:00:30,340 --> 00:00:32,500
Why are you spouting nonsense and crying?

11
00:00:32,870 --> 00:00:33,870
Mom.

12
00:00:35,010 --> 00:00:36,440
I don't have a twin, right?

13
00:00:37,610 --> 00:00:40,410
Of course you don't.
Who's been telling you such nonsense?

14
00:00:40,680 --> 00:00:41,750
Where did you hear that?

15
00:00:42,010 --> 00:00:46,180
Don't tell me she saw Oh Jang Mi.
Or worse, did she meet her?

16
00:00:46,250 --> 00:00:48,320
I met a woman who looked exactly like me.

17
00:00:48,820 --> 00:00:51,560
If I have a twin
and we're somehow connected,

18
00:00:52,320 --> 00:00:54,290
I feel like something
just happened to her.

19
00:00:54,860 --> 00:00:56,460
My heart aches so much.

20
00:01:12,240 --> 00:01:14,150
On January 17, at 9:47 a.m.,

21
00:01:15,180 --> 00:01:16,750
Mr. Oh Bok Gil was pronounced dead.

22
00:01:17,020 --> 00:01:18,050
No way...

23
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:20,990
Doctor...

24
00:01:26,020 --> 00:01:27,060
Oh, no.

25
00:01:30,630 --> 00:01:34,630
Dad, you can't go like this. You can't!

26
00:01:34,670 --> 00:01:37,840
Dad, open your eyes, please.

27
00:01:39,270 --> 00:01:42,670
Dad, what am I going to do?

28
00:01:43,110 --> 00:01:44,580
Wake up!

29
00:01:44,610 --> 00:01:45,610
Dad.

30
00:01:45,610 --> 00:01:46,910
Dad.

31
00:01:47,980 --> 00:01:49,910
- Dad.
- Father.

32
00:01:49,910 --> 00:01:50,950
Dad!

33
00:01:51,220 --> 00:01:56,150
This can't be happening!
This isn't right! Dad!

34
00:01:56,750 --> 00:01:59,460
I didn't even get to say goodbye,

35
00:02:00,060 --> 00:02:02,590
and I never got to tell you I love you.

36
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:04,960
Wake up! No!

37
00:02:05,230 --> 00:02:06,830
Our poor father.

38
00:02:07,470 --> 00:02:09,030
I feel so sorry for Dad. What do I do?

39
00:02:09,270 --> 00:02:10,370
- This can't be happening.
- Dad...

40
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:14,310
You can't die, Bok Gil.
You were too precious.

41
00:02:14,740 --> 00:02:19,640
- Bok Gil, hurry and open your eyes!
- Dad...

42
00:02:19,710 --> 00:02:20,950
Bok Gil...

43
00:02:21,710 --> 00:02:23,820
Dad.

44
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:25,950
Open your eyes!

45
00:02:29,790 --> 00:02:31,060
No way...

46
00:02:45,470 --> 00:02:46,740
Mom.

47
00:02:46,740 --> 00:02:48,070
Seriously...

48
00:02:48,970 --> 00:02:50,410
I don't have a twin, right?

49
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:54,010
I have no idea what nonsense
you're talking about.

50
00:02:54,750 --> 00:02:57,950
I gave birth to you.
I'm the one who gave birth to you.

51
00:02:58,550 --> 00:03:02,090
You think the mother who gave birth to you
wouldn't know if you had a twin?

52
00:03:02,290 --> 00:03:03,790
But it could happen, you know.

53
00:03:04,090 --> 00:03:05,260
On TV shows,

54
00:03:05,260 --> 00:03:07,760
babies are stolen at birth
from the hospital.

55
00:03:07,860 --> 00:03:11,100
You're just talking nonsense.
Are you making up stories now?

56
00:03:11,730 --> 00:03:13,260
Instead of spouting nonsense,

57
00:03:13,260 --> 00:03:14,600
go help General Manager Kang
and learn the ropes.

58
00:03:14,730 --> 00:03:18,440
Which hospital was I born in?
I'll look into it myself.

59
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:21,370
The way you're freaking out like this
is suspicious.

60
00:03:22,040 --> 00:03:24,580
Which hospital was I born in?

61
00:03:24,580 --> 00:03:26,380
Will you stop with this nonsense?

62
00:03:26,780 --> 00:03:28,280
What has gotten into you all of a sudden?

63
00:03:29,580 --> 00:03:30,580
Mom!

64
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:39,520
Seo Rin.

65
00:03:40,490 --> 00:03:42,530
Why do you keep asking things like that?

66
00:03:42,990 --> 00:03:44,200
Something's definitely suspicious.

67
00:03:44,660 --> 00:03:46,530
She's definitely hiding something.

68
00:03:46,530 --> 00:03:48,370
At the hotel the other day,

69
00:03:48,630 --> 00:03:52,600
a strange man and woman mistook me
for their daughter,

70
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:54,910
so of course it made me wonder
if I had a twin.

71
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:56,710
It just popped into my head.

72
00:03:58,410 --> 00:03:59,480
That's it?

73
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:02,480
There are so many people
in the world who look alike.

74
00:04:02,650 --> 00:04:04,020
If that's all it takes to be a twin,

75
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:06,750
then everyone in the world
who looks alike would be twins.

76
00:04:07,550 --> 00:04:09,290
Enough of this nonsense. Get out.

77
00:04:09,290 --> 00:04:10,390
I need to work.

78
00:04:29,740 --> 00:04:31,940
- Manager Lee.
- Is something wrong?

79
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:35,280
Finally,

80
00:04:36,450 --> 00:04:40,320
- the time has come.
- I'm sorry? What do you mean?

81
00:04:42,790 --> 00:04:43,790
(CEO's Office)

82
00:04:43,890 --> 00:04:46,890
We'll talk later.
This isn't a conversation for the phone.

83
00:04:56,470 --> 00:04:59,170
How on earth did Seo Rin
find out she has a twin?

84
00:05:14,350 --> 00:05:16,990
I either have to get Oh Jang Mi
away from Seo Rin,

85
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:20,660
or get her out of sight immediately.

86
00:05:21,590 --> 00:05:23,800
I can't live with this ticking time bomb.

87
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:30,800
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

88
00:05:34,970 --> 00:05:36,510
What does she mean, "The time has come?"

89
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:39,080
Why did Mom freak out like that?

90
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:44,850
Shit. Why am I crying again?

91
00:05:46,150 --> 00:05:48,950
There's definitely something more to this.

92
00:05:50,290 --> 00:05:51,490
Okay, I need to think.

93
00:05:51,990 --> 00:05:52,990
Think.

94
00:05:56,460 --> 00:05:58,030
You're not Jang Mi.

95
00:05:58,660 --> 00:06:00,060
You're pretending to be Jang Mi.

96
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:02,400
- You're not Jang Mi.
- What's with this woman?

97
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:05,470
Oh, you're not Jang Mi.

98
00:06:05,470 --> 00:06:06,470
I'm sorry.

99
00:06:06,470 --> 00:06:08,040
I mistook you for someone else.

100
00:06:10,010 --> 00:06:11,510
So Oh Jang Mi's father, Oh Bok Gil,

101
00:06:12,110 --> 00:06:14,510
went to the hotel to meet my mom
and saw me.

102
00:06:15,050 --> 00:06:18,250
When Mr. Oh confronted my mom
about why I look exactly like Jang Mi,

103
00:06:18,450 --> 00:06:20,650
my mom must have hit him with that wrench.

104
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:25,520
But then why is he in the hospital
for a car accident?

105
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:27,490
And why is Professor Kang
being blamed for it?

106
00:06:34,230 --> 00:06:35,230
Chef Kim.

107
00:06:35,670 --> 00:06:38,270
Regarding the Course A for our VIP dinner
reservation tonight,

108
00:06:40,170 --> 00:06:43,370
don't final sear the sous vide lamb
until you confirm the guests have arrived.

109
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:45,040
Make sure the sauce isn't too runny.

110
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:47,510
Adjust the consistency until it leaves
a slight sheen on the plate.

111
00:06:48,910 --> 00:06:51,520
Also, the full floor report for tonight...

112
00:06:52,150 --> 00:06:53,180
brought directly to me before we close.

113
00:06:54,350 --> 00:06:55,420
Okay.

114
00:06:58,090 --> 00:07:01,330
You're busy enough as general manager.
Are you still running the restaurant too?

115
00:07:02,030 --> 00:07:03,660
You're such a workaholic, Jun Ho.

116
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:07,500
Manager Lee.

117
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:10,840
You said to let you know
if I ran into any trouble, didn't you?

118
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,810
Could you do me a favor
and get Director Ma out of my hair?

119
00:07:14,540 --> 00:07:16,510
She's so distracting
I can't get any work done.

120
00:07:16,570 --> 00:07:20,280
- All right. I'm a busy woman myself.
- Never mind.

121
00:07:20,610 --> 00:07:21,910
It appears she's leaving
of her own accord.

122
00:07:23,710 --> 00:07:25,850
I'm going through some stuff,
so I wanted to hang out with you.

123
00:07:26,250 --> 00:07:28,550
You've gotten so much more uptight
since you became the general manager.

124
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:40,970
Geum Soon, I'm going out.

125
00:07:40,970 --> 00:07:42,770
Meanwhile, you go to the market...

126
00:07:42,770 --> 00:07:44,770
and get Chairman Ma's favorite
fresh croaker,

127
00:07:44,770 --> 00:07:46,740
and make some spicy croaker stew.

128
00:07:47,370 --> 00:07:50,170
And while you're at it,
make spicy squid salad...

129
00:07:50,370 --> 00:07:52,440
that my daughter Hong Ju likes.

130
00:07:56,510 --> 00:07:57,580
Why aren't you answering me?

131
00:07:58,320 --> 00:08:00,890
Yes, I heard you.

132
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:03,520
What kind of attitude is that?

133
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:06,990
Are you mocking me?

134
00:08:07,890 --> 00:08:09,130
Do you not know who I am?

135
00:08:09,490 --> 00:08:14,070
I, Yeom San Wol, am now the lady
of the Dream Group estate.

136
00:08:14,370 --> 00:08:17,640
Who's arguing with you?
Just go, have a nice time.

137
00:08:24,580 --> 00:08:26,140
Unbelievable.

138
00:08:28,080 --> 00:08:30,280
Director Ma asked if she had a twin?

139
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:31,680
She did.

140
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:35,090
I have no idea how much Seo Rin knows,

141
00:08:35,690 --> 00:08:38,090
and how she even got on
to the subject of a twin.

142
00:08:38,590 --> 00:08:39,620
I'm losing my mind.

143
00:08:41,060 --> 00:08:42,190
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

144
00:08:42,290 --> 00:08:45,300
Do you think
she might have met Oh Jang Mi?

145
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:48,000
- I don't know.
- No, that can't be it.

146
00:08:48,270 --> 00:08:49,730
They couldn't have met.

147
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:52,440
If they had,
Oh Jang Mi wouldn't have kept quiet.

148
00:08:52,940 --> 00:08:55,610
She would have come straight to me
and made a scene.

149
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:59,980
What if only Seo Rin saw her?

150
00:09:01,350 --> 00:09:04,120
- That's possible.
- The day Oh Jang Mi finds out,

151
00:09:05,020 --> 00:09:08,120
she'll find out
we tried to kill Jung Suk Hee.

152
00:09:08,620 --> 00:09:10,120
If that happens, we're in huge trouble.

153
00:09:10,420 --> 00:09:12,260
Everything will go up in smoke.

154
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:14,360
Everything we've built until now.

155
00:09:14,990 --> 00:09:16,090
Before that can happen,

156
00:09:16,660 --> 00:09:18,300
shouldn't we get rid of Oh Jang Mi?

157
00:09:19,430 --> 00:09:20,430
Of course we should.

158
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:23,170
We just have to pick the right moment.

159
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:24,870
And about Seo Rin...

160
00:09:25,470 --> 00:09:26,770
We need to keep a close eye on her.

161
00:09:27,540 --> 00:09:29,140
See how much she knows.

162
00:09:29,940 --> 00:09:30,940
Yes, ma'am.

163
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:37,280
Hello.

164
00:09:39,050 --> 00:09:40,050
Really?

165
00:09:43,490 --> 00:09:44,490
What is it?

166
00:09:45,190 --> 00:09:46,190
Don't tell me...

167
00:09:47,160 --> 00:09:48,160
Yes.

168
00:09:49,060 --> 00:09:50,460
Oh Bok Gil is dead.

169
00:09:54,270 --> 00:09:56,170
It seems luck is on our side after all.

170
00:09:57,670 --> 00:10:00,500
You think Professor Kang Nam Bong
will keep his mouth shut?

171
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:03,470
He won't.
I met with him and laid down the law.

172
00:10:04,310 --> 00:10:06,540
Besides, I already put in a word
with the police chief.

173
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:08,050
Right.

174
00:10:08,780 --> 00:10:10,150
So the case will be closed, then.

175
00:10:11,380 --> 00:10:14,020
- That's one less thing to worry about.
- Right?

176
00:10:15,750 --> 00:10:16,890
This calls for a celebration.

177
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:20,560
And send a wreath to the funeral home.
Make it the biggest one they have.

178
00:10:32,970 --> 00:10:34,570
Sounds like someone's at the door.

179
00:10:35,670 --> 00:10:37,170
Didn't you hear the doorbell?

180
00:10:39,780 --> 00:10:40,780
Good grief...

181
00:10:41,410 --> 00:10:42,580
Who is it?

182
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:47,890
Oh no...

183
00:10:48,820 --> 00:10:49,820
What do you think you're doing?

184
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:51,260
You murderer!

185
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:54,760
My dad is dead because of you.
Bring him back!

186
00:10:55,030 --> 00:10:57,900
- Bring him back, I said!
- Oh my gosh!

187
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:03,170
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

188
00:11:12,610 --> 00:11:14,110
"Closed due to a death in the family..."

189
00:11:16,580 --> 00:11:17,980
So Oh Bok Gil died.

190
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:21,520
So who's the murderer then?

191
00:11:23,020 --> 00:11:24,890
My mom, who hit him with the wrench?

192
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:27,560
Or Professor Kang Nam Bong,
who ran him over?

193
00:11:36,370 --> 00:11:39,500
Bring my dad back! You murderer!

194
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:43,710
Murderer? Who are you calling a murderer?
Let go of him and talk, you hear me?

195
00:11:43,710 --> 00:11:44,880
Let go of me.

196
00:11:45,110 --> 00:11:46,740
You're the one who murdered my father,

197
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:48,750
why aren't you in jail?
What are you doing here?

198
00:11:49,010 --> 00:11:51,680
Let go of him! Or I'm calling the police!

199
00:11:54,390 --> 00:11:55,550
You've been drinking?

200
00:11:57,350 --> 00:12:00,220
Are you toasting to my father's death?

201
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:01,860
Tell me.

202
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:04,060
That's enough.

203
00:12:04,260 --> 00:12:06,500
It's a tragic loss,

204
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:08,600
but it was just a case
of bad luck for the both of us.

205
00:12:08,770 --> 00:12:11,140
- What was that?
- Your father was drunk...

206
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:14,000
and lying in the middle of the street.
That's why the accident happened.

207
00:12:14,070 --> 00:12:15,740
Do you think I'm drinking for fun?

208
00:12:15,870 --> 00:12:19,740
I'm suffering too, you know?
It was just bad luck for both of us,

209
00:12:19,810 --> 00:12:21,280
so why are you causing such a scene?

210
00:12:21,610 --> 00:12:22,610
A scene?

211
00:12:23,380 --> 00:12:25,120
You killed someone, and you call this
"causing a scene?"

212
00:12:26,350 --> 00:12:29,590
You should be in prison.
How dare you raise your voice at me?

213
00:12:30,890 --> 00:12:33,090
You killed a man!

214
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:35,060
You killed a man!

215
00:12:35,190 --> 00:12:37,730
Tae Pyung, my father's being investigated
without detention.

216
00:12:37,730 --> 00:12:38,730
He's going to trial.

217
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:41,770
- So just stop. Please, calm down.
- Shut up!

218
00:12:43,670 --> 00:12:47,140
You're the one who should shut up!
Stay away from my family!

219
00:12:47,470 --> 00:12:49,070
He's presumed innocent
until proven guilty,

220
00:12:49,410 --> 00:12:51,440
so you have no right
to come here and act like this!

221
00:12:51,810 --> 00:12:53,340
If you ever cause a scene like this again,

222
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:58,620
there's no telling what I'll do
to your sister, Oh Jang Mi! You hear me?

223
00:13:00,550 --> 00:13:01,550
Let's go.

224
00:13:02,250 --> 00:13:03,850
You're the chief mourner.
You can't be here doing this.

225
00:13:23,010 --> 00:13:24,010
Baek Ho!

226
00:13:24,710 --> 00:13:25,810
Where are you going?

227
00:13:26,210 --> 00:13:28,780
You're not on their side.
You're part of this family.

228
00:13:29,010 --> 00:13:31,320
Mom, what are you talking about?

229
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,880
Jang Mi's father passed away.

230
00:13:34,350 --> 00:13:36,490
The least we can do is
show some respect for the dead!

231
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:40,220
Why did he have to pass away?

232
00:13:41,490 --> 00:13:42,630
What are we going to do, honey?

233
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,000
Oh my...

234
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:56,010
Are you his family?

235
00:13:56,340 --> 00:13:59,040
Didn't you head to
the funeral hall this morning?

236
00:14:00,210 --> 00:14:02,110
The patient who was here, Mr. Oh Bok Gil.

237
00:14:02,910 --> 00:14:04,780
Which funeral home was he taken to?

238
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:07,380
You must be her twin.

239
00:14:08,150 --> 00:14:09,320
Mr. Oh Bok Gil...

240
00:14:10,220 --> 00:14:11,720
passed away this morning.

241
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:15,460
He was moved to
our hospital's funeral home.

242
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:16,730
You should hurry over there.

243
00:14:21,930 --> 00:14:22,970
Shit.

244
00:14:24,130 --> 00:14:26,870
So I guess Oh Jang Mi
and I really are twins.

245
00:14:28,770 --> 00:14:29,770
Then...

246
00:14:30,610 --> 00:14:32,980
Does that mean the man
who might be my father is dead?

247
00:14:35,310 --> 00:14:36,380
I'm so lost right now.

248
00:14:37,980 --> 00:14:39,750
I have no idea what's going on.

249
00:14:48,590 --> 00:14:49,630
Dad...

250
00:14:51,830 --> 00:14:55,600
I never imagined
he would leave us like this.

251
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:57,270
What am I going to do?

252
00:14:58,870 --> 00:15:01,210
How could this happen?

253
00:15:01,940 --> 00:15:04,640
This isn't fair, Dad.

254
00:15:09,150 --> 00:15:11,650
My little Jang Mi
is finally starting elementary school.

255
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:14,250
That backpack's so big.
Are you sure you can carry it?

256
00:15:15,220 --> 00:15:16,390
You are...

257
00:15:16,990 --> 00:15:19,160
the daughter of my heart.

258
00:15:20,790 --> 00:15:22,260
No matter what anyone says,
you're my daughter.

259
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:31,100
Tae Sook.

260
00:15:31,340 --> 00:15:35,270
I never even got to tell Dad I love him.

261
00:15:36,070 --> 00:15:38,440
I can't let him go.

262
00:15:39,910 --> 00:15:42,480
How can I let him go?

263
00:15:42,850 --> 00:15:45,050
I really can't believe this.

264
00:15:53,260 --> 00:15:55,190
(May He Rest in Peace)

265
00:15:55,260 --> 00:15:56,430
What are you doing here?

266
00:15:58,100 --> 00:15:59,960
Don't let Kang Baek Ho in here.

267
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:03,200
- Don't let him set foot in here.
- Please, just stop.

268
00:16:11,910 --> 00:16:14,680
(May He Rest in Peace)

269
00:16:17,380 --> 00:16:18,380
I know...

270
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:20,220
it's painful for you to see me.

271
00:16:21,690 --> 00:16:23,290
But please,

272
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:26,320
let me pay my last respects.

273
00:16:29,330 --> 00:16:31,260
I was very fond of your father too.

274
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:34,470
He was someone...

275
00:16:35,630 --> 00:16:37,000
I truly respected...

276
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,270
and admired.

277
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:46,140
Jang Mi, I'm so sorry.

278
00:16:48,850 --> 00:16:50,110
I'm truly sorry.

279
00:16:50,650 --> 00:16:51,650
Baek Ho.

280
00:16:52,850 --> 00:16:55,150
This isn't your fault.

281
00:16:56,590 --> 00:16:58,590
You don't have to be sorry anymore.

282
00:16:59,860 --> 00:17:01,460
Just pay your respects to my dad...

283
00:17:02,460 --> 00:17:03,760
and then please leave quietly.

284
00:17:05,330 --> 00:17:07,030
Thank you for understanding, Jang Mi.

285
00:17:07,330 --> 00:17:08,330
And...

286
00:17:10,130 --> 00:17:11,200
From now on...

287
00:17:12,670 --> 00:17:14,840
I think it's best
if we don't see each other again.

288
00:17:16,510 --> 00:17:17,880
For both of our families' sakes,

289
00:17:19,710 --> 00:17:20,910
that would be for the best.

290
00:17:21,410 --> 00:17:22,550
Jang Mi...

291
00:17:26,180 --> 00:17:27,280
Oh Jang Mi.

292
00:17:27,890 --> 00:17:30,090
How can she look exactly like me?

293
00:17:32,020 --> 00:17:33,520
It looks like she's in love with that guy.

294
00:17:34,290 --> 00:17:36,260
But for them to be tangled up
in such a tragic fate,

295
00:17:36,760 --> 00:17:38,260
did my mom have a hand in it?

296
00:17:40,130 --> 00:17:43,300
(May He Rest in Peace)

297
00:17:43,770 --> 00:17:45,600
No. I don't know.

298
00:17:45,900 --> 00:17:49,410
First things first, I need to find out
if Oh Jang Mi and I are really twins.

299
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:54,180
Are you okay, honey?

300
00:17:55,280 --> 00:17:57,310
Someone died because of me,
so yes, I guess.

301
00:17:58,620 --> 00:18:00,080
But that's really strange.

302
00:18:00,750 --> 00:18:02,420
If the victim died,

303
00:18:03,490 --> 00:18:05,190
the police would've called you by now,

304
00:18:05,190 --> 00:18:07,960
despite the fact
that you had already been questioned.

305
00:18:08,490 --> 00:18:11,090
Why isn't there any word from them?
It's making me more anxious.

306
00:18:11,830 --> 00:18:15,270
It's all because CEO Chae
pulled some strings.

307
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:17,270
The police must have figured it out.

308
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:20,240
That you're innocent, right?

309
00:18:21,540 --> 00:18:24,240
I guess so.

310
00:18:24,680 --> 00:18:25,680
That's true.

311
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:29,080
Besides, for a minor case like this,

312
00:18:29,510 --> 00:18:31,050
there's probably nothing more
for them to investigate.

313
00:18:31,380 --> 00:18:35,120
The footage of the accident
is right there on your dashcam.

314
00:18:35,290 --> 00:18:36,590
What else could they possibly question?

315
00:18:41,190 --> 00:18:43,660
Anyway, I'm worried about Baek Ho.

316
00:18:44,360 --> 00:18:48,100
He might end up getting torn to pieces
at the funeral hall.

317
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:49,970
It's so upsetting.

318
00:18:53,540 --> 00:18:56,840
Chairman, the victim of the car accident
involving Professor Kang Nam Bong...

319
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:58,010
has passed away today.

320
00:18:59,280 --> 00:19:00,310
Is that so?

321
00:19:01,080 --> 00:19:03,910
Yes. But apparently,
CEO Chae pulled some strings...

322
00:19:03,980 --> 00:19:05,620
to keep him from being taken into custody.

323
00:19:07,220 --> 00:19:09,390
So you're telling me CEO Chae did that?

324
00:19:11,620 --> 00:19:13,420
Oh my goodness. Chairman.

325
00:19:14,420 --> 00:19:15,660
I didn't know you were here all alone.

326
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:21,630
I'm sorry.

327
00:19:21,900 --> 00:19:26,670
I was just out buying some golf clothes.
Since you said you'd teach me,

328
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:28,440
I'm just so excited!

329
00:19:28,970 --> 00:19:32,640
- Good for you.
- Will you really teach me tomorrow?

330
00:19:32,780 --> 00:19:35,550
Of course. You need to learn quickly,
Mrs. Yeom,

331
00:19:35,780 --> 00:19:37,780
so you can join me out on the green.

332
00:19:38,220 --> 00:19:39,580
I can't wait!

333
00:19:44,190 --> 00:19:45,660
Oh my, who was that?

334
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:49,090
- Isn't that Seo Rin?
- She just walked in.

335
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:51,900
But it looks like she's leaving,
wearing mourning clothes.

336
00:19:52,760 --> 00:19:53,930
I wonder who died.

337
00:19:54,460 --> 00:19:55,500
Mourning clothes?

338
00:20:08,450 --> 00:20:10,080
Chae Hwa Young! It was you, wasn't it?

339
00:20:10,410 --> 00:20:12,980
You tried to kill my Suk Hee
and Jang Mi, didn't you?

340
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:15,890
Why? Just tell me why!

341
00:20:17,220 --> 00:20:18,320
Oh Bok Gil.

342
00:20:18,820 --> 00:20:20,390
You asked me why, didn't you?

343
00:20:21,330 --> 00:20:22,890
It was the only way for me to survive.

344
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:25,030
Thirty years ago,

345
00:20:25,460 --> 00:20:29,270
if Jung Suk Hee and Oh Jang Mi had died,
none of this would've happened.

346
00:20:30,230 --> 00:20:32,740
That's the price you pay for learning
something you shouldn't have.

347
00:20:41,210 --> 00:20:42,280
Don't you dare blame me.

348
00:20:43,050 --> 00:20:47,180
This is all because of your wife,
Jung Suk Hee. It's not my fault.

349
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:48,720
You vile witch!

350
00:20:49,020 --> 00:20:51,190
How dare you blame anyone else?
This is because of your greed!

351
00:20:52,020 --> 00:20:54,760
You stole the twins
just to satisfy your own greed.

352
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:57,560
You stole my poor Suk Hee's baby.

353
00:20:57,560 --> 00:20:59,230
Have you been living well all this time?

354
00:20:59,330 --> 00:21:03,530
You shameless wretch.
You drove my Suk Hee to that state,

355
00:21:03,630 --> 00:21:06,970
you tore the twins apart
and forced them to live separately.

356
00:21:07,900 --> 00:21:08,910
Let go!

357
00:21:09,270 --> 00:21:11,440
And as if that wasn't enough,
you killed me?

358
00:21:11,740 --> 00:21:13,910
Now you'll die.
It's time to pay for your sins.

359
00:21:14,010 --> 00:21:16,850
You killed me,
so now I'm taking you with me.

360
00:21:17,080 --> 00:21:19,520
Die!

361
00:21:19,580 --> 00:21:22,490
Save me!

362
00:21:32,630 --> 00:21:34,630
(May He Rest in Peace)

363
00:21:41,040 --> 00:21:43,910
- You must be heartbroken.
- Ma'am.

364
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:47,210
Thank you for coming.

365
00:21:48,410 --> 00:21:50,580
Your father is in a better place now.

366
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:52,780
Stay strong, Tae Pyung.

367
00:21:53,380 --> 00:21:54,380
I will.

368
00:21:56,090 --> 00:21:57,290
Ma'am.

369
00:21:58,860 --> 00:22:01,020
Thank you so much for coming
when you're so busy.

370
00:22:01,590 --> 00:22:02,630
Jang Mi.

371
00:22:02,960 --> 00:22:04,630
I can't believe this happened so suddenly.

372
00:22:06,530 --> 00:22:08,730
There are no words.

373
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:16,940
Don't hold it in. It's okay to cry.

374
00:22:17,510 --> 00:22:19,540
If you can't cry today, when can you?

375
00:22:20,540 --> 00:22:22,010
It's not good to bottle it up.

376
00:22:24,410 --> 00:22:25,720
Even I'm this heartbroken,

377
00:22:26,580 --> 00:22:28,420
so I can't imagine
what you're going through.

378
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:41,200
- Go away.
- Mom, what's wrong? I'm right here.

379
00:22:41,260 --> 00:22:44,070
Mom, calm down. Mom, I'm right here.

380
00:22:44,130 --> 00:22:47,270
He's scary. Go away!

381
00:22:47,270 --> 00:22:50,010
He's scaring me. Go away!

382
00:22:50,010 --> 00:22:52,240
Manager Lee, sorry,
would you mind leaving here?

383
00:22:53,840 --> 00:22:54,850
It's okay.

384
00:22:57,380 --> 00:22:58,380
I'm sorry.

385
00:23:00,850 --> 00:23:03,220
Mom, it's okay. He's gone.

386
00:23:03,790 --> 00:23:04,820
It's okay.

387
00:23:05,360 --> 00:23:06,490
He's gone.

388
00:23:08,660 --> 00:23:10,590
- We're so sorry.
- It's okay.

389
00:23:10,660 --> 00:23:11,730
What am I going to do?

390
00:23:26,410 --> 00:23:29,510
Just in case Mom recognizes my handbag.

391
00:23:42,330 --> 00:23:43,460
I'm so sorry.

392
00:23:43,530 --> 00:23:47,660
I don't know why she always acts like that
toward Manager Lee.

393
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:51,470
If only I had ended the meeting
sooner that day...

394
00:23:51,840 --> 00:23:56,210
and called your father right away,
maybe none of this would have happened.

395
00:23:56,910 --> 00:24:01,080
- I'm truly sorry, Jang Mi.
- No, please. Why would you say that?

396
00:24:02,250 --> 00:24:03,250
Anyway,

397
00:24:04,380 --> 00:24:06,120
I heard the person responsible
for your father's accident...

398
00:24:06,420 --> 00:24:08,080
turned himself in right away.

399
00:24:08,350 --> 00:24:11,660
Yes. But something feels off.

400
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:14,160
- What?
- My dad...

401
00:24:14,260 --> 00:24:16,660
never touched soju in his entire life.

402
00:24:18,060 --> 00:24:22,500
- Really?
- Yes. He only drank a little rice wine.

403
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:25,240
So it's strange
that he was supposedly that drunk.

404
00:24:25,940 --> 00:24:30,410
And on top of that, my dad called me
several times that day.

405
00:24:31,740 --> 00:24:32,740
Dad?

406
00:24:33,540 --> 00:24:34,910
Dad, what's wrong? Are you hurt?

407
00:24:37,750 --> 00:24:38,820
Jang Mi.

408
00:24:40,320 --> 00:24:41,380
Listen to me carefully.

409
00:24:43,320 --> 00:24:45,190
The one who did that to your mother...

410
00:24:47,160 --> 00:24:48,160
and you...

411
00:24:49,230 --> 00:24:50,290
You...

412
00:24:51,830 --> 00:24:52,830
Ssangkal...

413
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:56,270
"The one who did that to your mother..."

414
00:24:56,270 --> 00:24:57,470
"and you... Ssang..."

415
00:24:58,100 --> 00:24:59,100
Is that all?

416
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:03,510
Yes. I have no idea
what he was trying to say.

417
00:25:04,140 --> 00:25:06,680
And there are too many suspicious things
about his accident.

418
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:08,450
Really?

419
00:25:08,910 --> 00:25:10,850
But didn't the person responsible
turn himself in?

420
00:25:11,180 --> 00:25:13,320
Yes, that's true,

421
00:25:13,580 --> 00:25:17,550
but a few things don't add up,
so I'm going to go to the police station.

422
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:21,760
Jang Mi, you must be heartbroken
after losing your father.

423
00:25:21,990 --> 00:25:25,900
You shouldn't have to deal with this.
Let Manager Lee handle it.

424
00:25:26,330 --> 00:25:30,400
If you think something's not right,
I'll have him look into it for you.

425
00:25:30,900 --> 00:25:33,340
That means a lot. Thank you.

426
00:25:35,170 --> 00:25:36,940
Is Mom really such a hypocrite?

427
00:25:37,740 --> 00:25:40,540
She's saying she'll help Oh Jang Mi,
but it's all a lie.

428
00:25:41,340 --> 00:25:43,410
And she's the one
who hit Oh Jang Mi's father with a wrench.

429
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:49,320
Was everything okay after I left?

430
00:25:51,590 --> 00:25:52,590
It was fine.

431
00:25:52,890 --> 00:25:55,560
Oh Jang Mi's sister took her mother away,
so there won't be any trouble.

432
00:25:56,330 --> 00:25:57,990
Things seem quiet so far.

433
00:25:58,330 --> 00:25:59,900
I heard Jung Suk Hee's mind had regressed,

434
00:26:00,400 --> 00:26:02,430
but do you think she might be remembering
what happened?

435
00:26:03,030 --> 00:26:04,030
Who knows?

436
00:26:04,430 --> 00:26:06,140
I was on pins and needles earlier.

437
00:26:06,600 --> 00:26:09,670
I really thought she was about to spill
everything we did.

438
00:26:09,970 --> 00:26:11,210
"Everything we did?"

439
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:13,110
What on earth did they do?

440
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:17,410
Mom, what in the world did you do
to Oh Jang Mi's mother?

441
00:26:17,910 --> 00:26:20,220
Anyway, we dodged a bullet this time,

442
00:26:20,580 --> 00:26:23,090
but I have no idea
what's going to happen next.

443
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:25,520
They're like roaches.

444
00:26:25,520 --> 00:26:27,660
Just when I think I've gotten rid of them,
they crawl back out.

445
00:26:28,730 --> 00:26:30,630
I can never let my guard down.

446
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:34,430
If I have to see Oh Jang Mi again,
you stay away.

447
00:26:35,430 --> 00:26:37,230
- Understood.
- Then again,

448
00:26:38,070 --> 00:26:40,470
the best thing would be
to avoid seeing her altogether.

449
00:26:40,940 --> 00:26:44,980
Please, deal with her for good this time
so she never sees the light of day again.

450
00:26:50,510 --> 00:26:51,650
My own mother...

451
00:26:52,280 --> 00:26:53,920
Is this the kind of person she is?

452
00:27:40,660 --> 00:27:42,130
(The First Man)

453
00:27:42,330 --> 00:27:44,930
Did you find out why my dad went there?

454
00:27:45,070 --> 00:27:48,340
We found a man who bought soju
at a nearby corner store.

455
00:27:48,610 --> 00:27:50,640
Once we get the composite sketch,
we'll be able to find him in no time.

456
00:27:51,310 --> 00:27:54,180
First, I need to get a DNA test
to be certain.

457
00:27:54,510 --> 00:27:57,510
Once I get the DNA results,
everything will be clear.

458
00:27:57,850 --> 00:28:00,120
You're saying Seo Rin's been digging
into my past?

459
00:28:00,550 --> 00:28:03,490
Don't you think she's starting to question
whether she has a twin?

460
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:05,890
I'll have to keep a close eye on Seo Rin.

461
00:28:07,360 --> 00:28:09,360
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
